   517	## RESURRECTION
   518	In 1967, Tykodi (17) showed how entropy production theories might be not
   519	only salvaged, but made in a sense exact, using logic so simple and
   520	direct that one could not question any part of it without at the same
   521	time questioning a considerable part of established equilibrium theory.
   522	He simply abandoned altogether the notions of local equilibrium and
   523	local entropy production, and reasoned as follows.
   524	There is one case where logically impeccable inferences about an
   525	irreversible process were drawn from the relations of equilibrium
   526	theory: the Joule-Thomson porous plug experiment of 1852. The inflowing
   527	gas is at thermal equilibrium with temperature and pressure
   528	$(T_1, P_1)$, and we measure the outflowing gas far enough downstream
   529	from the plug so that it has come back to thermal equilibrium, with new
   530	values $(T_2, P_2)$. By a simple argument given in all the textbooks we
   531	are persuaded at once that however violent the irreversible process
