     7	  Mitchell. He argues that the traditional formulation of the principle is often
     8	  circular or restrictive, and proposes a reorientation based on predictive
     9	  statistical mechanics. In this framework, the "caliber" of a space-time process
    10	  (a generalized entropy functional over thermokinetic history) determines the
    11	  steady state and generating equations of motion for irreversible processes
    12	  through its variational properties, mirroring Gibbs' principle for
    13	  thermostatics.
